import TNLean.MPS.CanonicalForm.SectorComparison.CommonSectorTransport

/-!
# Structural after-blocking theorem for sector comparison

The structural common-period theorem and the common-sector transport theorems
give the canonical-form reduction after blocking:
the zero block remains a zero block, the nonzero blocks are transported to a
common family of cyclic-sector representatives, and the positive-length MPV
coefficients agree after the induced relabeling of blocked words.
-/
